condition.narrative: Finance Agreement :FIPAG to cover debt services requirements and to not incur any additional debt | Description :ProjectImplementing Entity shall ensure that it: covers 1.2 times its debt services requirements through its net revenues; and does notincur any additional debt unless a reasonable forecast of its revenues and expenditures show that its projected net revenues foreach FY during the term of the debt to be incurred shall be at least 1.5 times the projected debt service requirements.

Finance Agreement :FIPAG water tariffs to reflect principles of full cost recovery | Description :No later than twenty-four (24)months after Effective Date, Recipient shall ensure that tariffs for water systems under responsibility of FIPAG shall reflectprinciples of full cost recovery and be sufficient to cover operating expenses, depreciation, and cost ofcapital in a reasonabletime horizon for all said water systems. Tariffs will be assessed during mid-term review. | Due Date :23-Aug-2015

Finance Agreement :Water concession for Nacala Velha to be transferred to FIPAG | Description :No later than June 12, 2016, theRecipient shall transfer the water concession and assets of the water system in Nacala Velha to FIPAG. | Due Date :12-Jun-2016
